@startuml C4_Ecosystem_Partners
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Ecosystem - Strategic Partner Integration

Boundary(cloud_providers, "Cloud Providers") {
    Component(aws, "AWS", "Cloud", "EC2, RDS, S3")
    Component(gcp, "Google Cloud", "Cloud", "Compute, Firestore")
    Component(azure, "Microsoft Azure", "Cloud", "App Service, SQL")
}

Boundary(databases, "Database Partners") {
    Component(postgres, "PostgreSQL", "Database", "Primary DB")
    Component(mysql, "MySQL", "Database", "Alternative")
    Component(mongodb, "MongoDB", "Database", "NoSQL option")
}

Boundary(monitoring_partners, "Monitoring Partners") {
    Component(datadog, "Datadog", "APM", "Full observability")
    Component(newrelic, "New Relic", "APM", "Application monitoring")
    Component(splunk, "Splunk", "Log", "Enterprise logging")
}

Boundary(integration_partners, "Integration Partners") {
    Component(stripe, "Stripe", "Payments", "Payment processing")
    Component(okta, "Okta", "Auth", "Identity management")
    Component(slack, "Slack", "Messaging", "Notifications")
}

Boundary(performance_partners, "Performance Partners") {
    Component(redis, "Redis", "Cache", "Caching layer")
    Component(kafka, "Apache Kafka", "Streaming", "Event streaming")
    Component(elasticsearch, "Elasticsearch", "Search", "Full-text search")
}

Boundary(development_partners, "Development Ecosystem") {
    Component(github, "GitHub", "VCS", "Source control")
    Component(jira, "Jira", "Project Mgmt", "Issue tracking")
    Component(sonarqube, "SonarQube", "Code Quality", "Quality gates")
}

cloud_providers --> aws: "Integration"
databases --> postgres: "Supported"
monitoring_partners --> datadog: "Integrated"
integration_partners --> stripe: "Connected"
performance_partners --> redis: "Enabled"
development_partners --> github: "Native"

Note as N1
Strategic Partner Ecosystem:

Cloud Infrastructure:
- AWS: Preferred partner (EC2, RDS, S3)
- Google Cloud: GKE, Firestore
- Azure: App Service, SQL Database
- Multi-cloud: Kubernetes abstraction

Databases:
- PostgreSQL: Primary choice (ACID, JSON)
- MySQL: Compatible (alternative)
- MongoDB: Document database (optional)
- Integration: JDBC drivers

Monitoring & Observability:
- Datadog: Full APM + infrastructure
- New Relic: Application monitoring
- Splunk: Enterprise log aggregation
- OpenTelemetry: Standard protocol

Payment & Commerce:
- Stripe: Payment processing
- PayPal: Alternative payment
- Taxjar: Tax compliance

Authentication & Identity:
- Okta: Enterprise SSO
- Azure AD: Microsoft integration
- Auth0: Alternative IAM

Communication:
- Slack: Notifications + alerts
- Teams: Microsoft collaboration
- Twilio: SMS/voice

Caching & Streaming:
- Redis: Primary cache
- Memcached: Alternative
- Kafka: Event streaming
- RabbitMQ: Message broker

Search & Analytics:
- Elasticsearch: Full-text search
- Solr: Alternative
- ClickHouse: Columnar analytics

Development & DevOps:
- GitHub: Source control (primary)
- GitLab: Alternative SCM
- Jira: Issue tracking
- Confluence: Documentation
- SonarQube: Code quality
- Jenkins: CI/CD

Version Control Strategy:
- GitHub: Public + private repos
- Git flow: Feature branches
- Protected main branch
- Signed commits

Integration Patterns:
- REST APIs (primary)
- Webhooks (events)
- SDKs (when available)
- Direct database integration (rare)

Certification & Support:
- Partner certifications: AWS, GCP
- Technical account managers
- Preferred pricing
- Co-marketing agreements

Future Partners (2027):
- AI/ML: OpenAI, Anthropic
- Blockchain: Ethereum, Polygon
- Data: Databricks, Palantir
- Security: CrowdStrike, Palo Alto

Vendor Lock-in Mitigation:
- Use standards (Kubernetes, OpenTelemetry)
- Multi-cloud strategy
- Avoid proprietary APIs
- Maintain portability
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
